{
  "texts": [
    "Further, we consider tasks such as question answering and natural language inference that require a question or a hypothesis before generating the appropriate answer.",
    "Concurrent to this work, Yehudai et al. (2024) use in-context learning with Falcon-40B and Llama-65B to generate \"grounded tasks\" to adapt smaller models like FLAN-T5-XL (3B).",
    "These grounded tasks are similar to conditional tasks, except the instructions do not necessarily refer directly to the user's text.",
    "They might only be based on it, such as asking an open-ended question based on the original text.",
    "Our work goes further in several ways."
  ]
}